                            <comment id="14472643" author="rui.figueira" created="Sun, 18 Mar 2012 06:57:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m experiencing the same problem. As a workarround, I just declared a default runningScript property and it worked:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;MyConsole &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; Console
{
	&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt; scriptRunning = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt;
	
	void newScript(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;ClassLoader&lt;/span&gt; parent, Binding binding) {
		def importCustomizer = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ImportCustomizer()
                &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// add &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; classes
&lt;/span&gt;                ...
        }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14472585" author="rui.figueira" created="Sun, 18 Mar 2012 06:59:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Well, my mistake... it&apos;s not actually working properly...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473520" author="lau" created="Tue, 20 Nov 2012 17:20:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have the same problem. Could someone please explain at least why it isn&apos;t working.&lt;br/&gt;
The property is present in the super class, how does it dissapear. I am sorry&lt;br/&gt;
that I do not understand groovy very well. I am trying to learn. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473719" author="pschumacher" created="Tue, 1 Jan 2013 02:20:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Laurence: I guess the missing property exception occurs because scriptRunning is declared private in groovy.ui.console. This is probably related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-3010&quot; title=&quot;fix private field visibility&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-3010&quot;&gt;GROOVY-3010&lt;/a&gt; or some of the other open issues concerning private visibility.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473611" author="pschumacher" created="Tue, 1 Jan 2013 04:21:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I created a pull request &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/pull/100/files&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/pull/100/files&lt;/a&gt; which removes the private visibility of the scriptRunning and two others attributes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now the class should be extendable.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14473635" author="blackdrag" created="Fri, 4 Jan 2013 02:32:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;merged pull request&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
